A two-metre South American boa constrictor is on the loose after police mistakenly thought it was a harmless python .
The reptile was released into bushland at Surfers Paradise on March 26 .
A bizarre search is now unfolding on Queensland's Gold Coast as authorities try to locate the reptile .
It could be found 'within a month' but there are fears if the large-predatory boa has Inclusion Body Disease 'it can be unbelievably contagious if that gets loose in Australia'